comment: Green (LAC) makes contact with Durant's (OKC) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Aldrich (LAC) sets the screen on Foye (OKC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Adams (OKC) sets the screen on Green (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Aldrich (LAC) makes incidental contact with Durant (OKC) that does not affect his RSBQ. Durant then slips and falls to the floor.
Roberson (OKC) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Crawford (LAC) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Johnson (LAC) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Adams (OKC) makes incidental contact with Westbrook (OKC) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Aldrich (LAC) obtains a legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Foye (OKC) that does not affect his RSBQ.
R-SLA shows that Rivers (LAC) makes contact with Durant's (OKC) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Westbrook (OKC) cleanly strips the ball from Johnson (LAC).
Adams (OKC) sets the screen on Mbah a Moute (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Aldrich (LAC) and Adams (OKC) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Crawford (LAC) fumbles the ball and Durant (OKC) does not intentionally kick the ball on the play.
Durant (OKC) and Crawford (LAC) make incidental foot contact with one another.
Roberson (OKC) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Rivers (LAC) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Prigioni (LAC) dislodges Foye (OKC) during rebounding. Foye then makes contact with his teammate Westbrook (OKC), who secures the rebound and makes incidental contact with Rivers (LAC).
